/*!
\page random_randi RANDI Uniformly Distributed Integer

<p>
Section: \ref sec_random "Random Number Generation"
\section Usage
Generates an array of uniformly distributed integers between
the two supplied limits.  The general syntax for <tt>randi</tt> is
\verbatim
   y = randi(low,high)
\endverbatim
where <tt>low</tt> and <tt>high</tt> are arrays of integers.  Scalars
can be used for one of the arguments.  The output <tt>y</tt> is
a uniformly distributed pseudo-random number between <tt>low</tt>
and <tt>high</tt> (inclusive).
\section Example
Here is an example of a set of random integers between 
zero and 5:

\if FRAGMENT
frag_random_randi_000.m
0
randi(zeros(1,6),5*ones(1,6))
\endif


\verbinclude frag_random_randi_000.m.out 

*/
